In this context, and because pedigrees are rarely known a priori , we developed MetHis , a C open-source software package available athttps://github.com/romain- laurent/MetHis.MetHis simulates independent SNPs or microsatellite markers in an admixed population H under any version of the two-source populations general model from Verdu and Rosenberg (2011), and calculates summary-statistics of interest to the study of complex admixture processes (Supplementary Note S1 ).

After calculating fraction infectivities, we used the neutcurve Python package (https://jbloomlab.github.io/neutcurve/) to calculate the plasma dilution that inhibited infection by 50% (IC50) by fitting a Hill curve with the bottom fixed at 0 and the top fixed at 1. NT50s for each plasma sample were calculated as the reciprocal of the IC50.
